    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "Available for the discerning collector is an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) that represents the zenith of naturally aspirated Bavarian engineering. This example features the S54 3.2L inline-six power plant, utilizing six individual throttle bodies and high-pressure Double-VANOS variable valve timing to achieve a stratospheric 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox to a torque-sensing M-Variable limited-slip differential. Mechanically, this chassis is beyond reproach: the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced, and rod bearing prophylaxis has been performed to ensure long-term reciprocating assembly integrity. The suspension architecture remains tight, featuring aluminum control arms and factory-spec damping that preserves the car\u2019s legendary kinematics. Finished in its original factory paint with zero evidence of oxidation or clear coat failure, the cabin is trimmed in pristine Nappa leather with no detectable bolster wear. This is a turn-key, mechanically transparent specimen for the purist who demands peak performance and structural perfection.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
